â­ 4. How DNS Resolution Actually Works (Step-by-Step)

When you type app.example.com:

Browser checks local DNS cache

Browser asks Recursive Resolver (ISP/Google 8.8.8.8)

Resolver checks Root â†’ TLD (.com) â†’ Route 53 Nameserver

Route 53 returns the A-record or CNAME

Browser connects to returned IP or host

This entire process usually takes milliseconds.

â­ 5. TTL (Time to Live)

TTL determines how long DNS results are cached.

Short TTL (30 secâ€“1 min) â†’ good for dynamic apps or migrating servers

Long TTL (1 hr) â†’ good for stable services

TTL matters when you:

switch EC2 instance

switch ALB

do dev â†’ prod migrations

